On Groups Listed\nArt Supplies Leather\nSupplies Ceramic Sup\nplies Craft Supplies\nCraft Kits Metal\nEnameling Flower Mak\ning Paints Mosaics\nAll Soles Final\u2014No Charges\nNo Delietnf\nOPI.N DAII.r 'TIL fl r.M.\nSUPPLY COMPANY, INC.\n934 N.w York Avt. N.W. Wt. J 7900\nCONTRACT\nBRIDGE\nBy EASLEY BLACKWOOD\nMr. Helnslte Is not above ex-j\npecting his partner to drop\nsingleton Icings and doubleton\nqueens, even when there are\nfive or six cards of a suit out\nstanding. In most cases, of\ncourse, this is completely un\nreasonable. But there was an\nodd twist in today\u2019s deal which\nmade Mr. Heinsite\u2019s criticism\ncorrect and justified.\nSouth dealer.\nNeither side vulnerable.\nNORTH\n(Mr. Heinsite)\n*KJ7\nJlO 3\n0 J 10764\nA#\nWEST EAST\n(Mr. Dale) (Mrs. Keen)\n*843 10963\nK 8 6 5 3 <?A4\nOK 0853\n*Q1043 J 9 7 5\nSOUTH\n(Mr. Muzzy)\n*AQS\n?Q97\n0 AQ93\nKB3\nThe bidding:\nSouth West North East\nINT Pass 3NT All pass\nOpening lead: Five of hearts.!\nMr. Dale led the five of\nhearts and his partner won\nwith the ace and returned the\nfour. Here Mr. Dale made a\nthoughtful play. He could have\ngone up with the king and led\na third round of hearts, hoping\nto regain the lead later with\nthe king of diamonds. Instead\nhe ducked the trick to give\nthe impression that he had no\npossible side entries and that\nthe only way to reach his hand\nwas in the heart suit itself.\nDummy's 10 won the second\ntrick and Mr. Muzzy saw hej\nhad no chance for his contract\nunless he brought in the dia\nmonds. At trick three he led\na diamond from the board and\nfinessed the queen. Mr. Dale\nwon with the lone king and\ncashed three heart tricks to put\nthe hand down one.\n\"Bang down your ace of dia\nmonds\u2014don\u2019t take the finesse,\u201d j\nscreamed Mr. Heinsite.\n\u201cThat\u2019s ridiculous,\u201d Mr. j\nMuzzy replied. \u201cWith four dia- j\nmonds out, how could I be ex-!\npected to know Dale had a\nsingleton king?\u201d\nHe appealed to Mr. Dale to\nsupport his stand but the old\nmaster had to admit that this j\ntime (whether by chance or\nnot) Mr. Heinsite had some\nthing.\n\u201cHe\u2019s right, Muzzy,\" Mr. Dale i\nsaid. \u201cThe right play at the\nthird trick was to lay down\nthe ace of diamonds\u2014and not\nbecause you could figure me\nfor the lone king. The point\nis that you could afford to lose\na diamond trick to Mrs. Keen.\nIf she woh the second lead of\ndiamonds with the king she\nwould have no heart to return.\nOr if she did then the hearts\nwould be divided evenly and\nwe could win only three hearts\nand a diamond.\n\u201cYou could not afford to lose\na diamond to me. Now if I\nhad the king of diamonds,\nguarded, you were never going\nto make the hand. So you had\nnothing to lose by making a\nsafety play against the possi\nbility that I had the king all\nby itself.\u201d\n(Distributed by McNauaht Syndicate.)\nWORD GAME\nFind 37 or more words in\nQUADRATIC\nmeaning, \u201cresembling a square.\u201d\nAverage is 32 words; time limit,\n30 minutes.\nRule* the uni: 1. Words must be!\nof four or more letters. 2. Words which\nacquire four letters by the addition of t\nsuch as \"bats,\" \"cars.\" are not\nused. 3. Only one form of a word Is\nused. 4. Proper names are not used.\nAnswer ta LAPSING\nlain, lapln, lapis, ling, align, aping,\nnail, pain, paling pangs, ping, plain.,\nplan. sail. sang, sapling, sign, signal, i\nslag. slap. slip, sling, slang, slain, snag,\nsnail, snip, snap, span. spin, spinal.;\nnails, gains, gasp. j\nScientific Tuts Provo\n\"BC\u201d Starts\nFASTER\nto EASE PAIN\nIVi TIMIS\nFASTER then.v\nSTRAIGHT ASPIRIN\nOVM VA TIMIS\nViA7 TASTER than a\nlUFFERED ASPIRIN\nOVM 2 TIMIS\nVi\" FASTER than a\nCOMBINATION\nRELIEVER\n\n\u2022Recent tests by atf independent\nmedical research laboratory\nproved that in only ONE\nMINUTE the quantity of\u2019BC\"\nreaching the blood stream\n(where pain relief begins) far i\nexceeded three other pain\nrelievers tested. Now, more\nthan ever, you can be assured of\nthe fas